<%- include('partials/head') %>
<div class="ballot-head"><div class="bar"></div><div class="hairlines"></div></div>
<p class="eyebrow">Official secret ballot</p>
<h1>Cast your ballot</h1>
<p class="sub"><%= openCount %> vote<%= openCount === 1 ? ' is' : 's are' %> currently open.</p>

<form method="post" action="/vote" autocomplete="off">
  <label for="credential">Your one-time voting credential</label>
  <input type="text" id="credential" name="credential" placeholder="XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX"
         inputmode="latin" autocapitalize="characters" spellcheck="false" required
         style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: .12em; max-width: 420px;">
  <br>
  <button class="btn primary" type="submit">Open my ballot</button>
</form>

<div class="notice seal">
  <strong>Your vote is secret — by architecture, not by promise.</strong>
  You never enter your name here. Your credential was randomly generated, and your ballot is
  encrypted the instant it is cast and stored with no link to you, your credential, or the time
  you voted. Not even the election committee or the system administrator can see how you voted:
  opening the sealed ballots requires multiple key shares held by different people, and even then
  ballots carry no identity. The committee can see <em>that</em> you voted (as election observers
  are entitled to), never <em>how</em>.
</div>

<div class="notice">
  Lost or never received your credential? Contact the election committee — they will void the old
  one and issue a replacement. Per IAFF model rules, an alternative way to vote is available to any member who chooses not to
  vote electronically — ask the committee for a paper ballot.
</div>
<%- include('partials/foot') %>
